keywords.name: Close All Connections
keywords.shortdoc: Closes all open connections and empties the connection cache.

keywords.name: Close Connection
keywords.shortdoc: Closes the current Telnet connection and returns any remaining output.

keywords.name: Execute Command
keywords.shortdoc: Executes given command and reads and returns everything until prompt.

keywords.name: Login
keywords.shortdoc: Logs in to the Telnet server with the given user information.

keywords.args: host, alias=None, port=23, timeout=None, newline=None, prompt=None, prompt_is_regexp=False
keywords.name: Open Connection
keywords.shortdoc: Opens a new Telnet connection to the given host and port.

keywords.name: Read
keywords.shortdoc: Reads and returns/logs everything that is currently available in the output.

keywords.name: Read Until
keywords.shortdoc: Reads from the current output, until expected is encountered.

keywords.name: Read Until Prompt
keywords.shortdoc: Reads from the current output, until a prompt is found.

keywords.name: Read Until Regexp
keywords.shortdoc: Reads from the current output, until a match to a regexp in expected.

keywords.name: Set Default Log Level
keywords.shortdoc: Sets the default log level used by all read keywords.

keywords.name: Set Newline
keywords.shortdoc: Sets the newline used by the `Write` keyword.

keywords.name: Set Prompt
keywords.shortdoc: Sets the prompt used in this connection to `prompt`.

keywords.name: Set Timeout
keywords.shortdoc: Sets the timeout used in read operations to the given value.

keywords.name: Switch Connection
keywords.shortdoc: Switches between active connections using an index or alias.

keywords.name: Write
keywords.shortdoc: Writes the given text over the connection and appends a newline.

keywords.name: Write Bare
keywords.shortdoc: Writes the given text over the connection without appending a newline.

keywords.name: Write Until Expected Output
keywords.shortdoc: Writes the given text repeatedly, until `expected` appears in the output.
